116.9	Bob_Hope	Bob Hope	Bob Hope, KBE, KCSG, KSS (born Leslie Townes Hope; May 29, 1903 â€“ July 27, 2003) was a British-born American comedian and actor who appeared in vaudeville, on Broadway, and in radio, television and movies. He was also noted for his work with the US Armed Forces and his numerous USO shows entertaining American military personnel. Throughout his long career, he was honored for his humanitarian work. In 1996, the U.S. Congress honored Bob Hope by declaring him the "first and only honorary veteran of the U.S. armed forces." Bob Hope appeared in or hosted 199 known USO shows.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b1/Bob_Hope_in_The_Ghost_Breakers_trailer.JPG/225px-Bob_Hope_in_The_Ghost_Breakers_trailer.JPG
